President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Todd Sunhwae Kim to serve on the District of Columbia Court of Appeals. Kim is currently the Solicitor General of the District of Columbia and has held that position since 2006. He oversees appellate litigation for the District of Columbia government in various courts, including the D.C. Court of Appeals, the United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit, and the United States Supreme Court. Prior to his current role, Kim worked as an appellate attorney with the United States Department of Justice and served as a law clerk to Judge Judith Rogers of the United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit. He holds an A.B. magna cum laude from Harvard College and a J.D. magna cum laude from Harvard Law School. President Obama expressed confidence in Kim's ability, integrity, and independence.